<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Boanerges on 12-28-2001 02:15 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">My experience has been that if I were to reroll I'd go down the list...

AGI - you need to have 75 base AGI. Period. This is very important to your AC. At level 60, dropping below this costs almost 75 AC

STR - depends on how your character is going to go. If you're doing this solo then I'd put points into this to carry loot. If you're twinking or PLing, I'd ignore this.

STA - I wouldn't put too much into STA. It helps, but it's not going to make a massive difference unless you dump a lot of points here. Gives you more HP.

WIS - used to be everyone and their dog wished they had dumped into wis but the explosion in high wisdom items out there means it's a lot easier to pass 200 wis. Going past 200 has some benefits now but it's not something I would put any great efforts into.

DEX - affects procs and maybe hit percentages. Not real useful

CHA - The "other" green stat. Supposedly affects Death Pact, Divine Intervention and the (useless) Lull series. Also affects buy/sell prices. Again, not really useful for starting points.

INT - might affect tradeskills. Not useful


Hope that helps.


------------------
Boanerges Thundercry
High Priest of Prexus
[URL=http://www.cohort.cc]Cohort Chalybeius[/URL]
Cazic Thule Server</TEXTAREA>
